2019", shape=ellipse, URL="RFC8583.html", target="_top", tooltip="RFC 7068 describes requirements for Overload Control in Diameter.  This includes a requirement to allow Diameter nodes to send load information, even when the node is not overloaded.  The base solution defined in RFC 7683 (Diameter Overload Information Conveyance (DOIC)) describes a mechanism meeting most of the requirements but does not currently include the ability to send load information.  This document defines a mechanism for the conveying of Diameter load information."];
